  "enhanced_information": "INH (isoniazid) is known to cause neuropathy primarily through its interference with the metabolism of pyridoxine (vitamin B6), leading to its depletion. This depletion results in nerve damage and subsequent neuropathy. Supplementation with pyridoxine is the standard treatment to counteract this effect, as it replenishes vitamin B6, restores normal nerve function, and reduces symptoms of neuropathy. The evidence paths confirm that pyridoxine treats neuropathy and is associated with the uptake processes affected by isoniazid. Other vitamins like thiamine, niacin, and riboflavin do not have clear, direct evidence supporting their use in treating INH-induced neuropathy, and their roles in this specific condition remain uncertain or unsupported by current medical consensus."
